data.message: Applying to EECS be like

When do we beat Stanfurd at the Big Game? They're laughing at us, at our brilliance. And now they are beating us athletically. They're not our friend, believe me. They are beating us athletically. The UC has become a dumping ground for everyone else's problems.

It's true. These are the best and finest. When Stanfurd sends its people, they're not sending their best. They're not sending you. They're not sending you. They're bringing people that have lots of problems, and they're bringing those problems with them. They're bringing elitism. They're spoiled. They're bringing grade inflation. And some, I assume, are good people.

But I speak to football players and they tell us what they're getting. And it only makes sense. It makes common sense. They're not sending us the right people. It's coming from more than Stanfurd. It's coming from all over Palo Alto and San Jose, and it's coming probably, probably from UCLA. Because we have no protection and no confidence we don't know what's happening. And it's got to stop and it's got to stop fast.
